posts.cooked: Can the frc 2022 ball be jammed?

posts.name: EricH
posts.cooked:
Context?

I would say that it is possible to jam it into something, yes. Or to use it to jam something. I want to say at least a few robots got one stuck in a really bad spot somewhere along the line, though the bouncy nature of the ball tended to keep it out of most of those.

If you’re asking if it’s compressible, it is, though not all that much.

posts.name: GaryVoshol
posts.cooked:
OK, back on track.

Any soft rubbery inflated ball can be compressed. It just depends on how much. Compress it too much and it will pop.

Yes, the 2022 ball could be compressed.

posts.name: Elliot S
posts.cooked:
dorukbzn:

Can the frc 2022 ball be jammed?

Make sure your ball is compressed at all times. If there is a dead spot, the ball will find it. But for us at least feeding another ball into the robot fixed it 99% of the time.

I recommend a minimum compression of 9.3" with a max of 8.75" on non shooter parts, but that is all subjective.

The max compression I have seen is 8" on 1678’s Shooter link here:

Sign in to Onshape, the #1 fastest growing CAD system in the world with over 4 million users.

Also to add to some points posed above: From my experience, it is almost impossible to pop it from the outside. The ball will stop feeding before it pops inside your robot.
